text.Prompt: Can you tell me how to avoid getting bunions?
text.Response A:
Avoid narrow shoes.
Don't wear high heels.
Always choose well-fitting shoes.
Walk around the house in bare feet.
Use cold therapy.
Apply a splint.
Maintain a healthy weight.
See a podiatrist.
Find a chiropractor or osteopath.
Consider physical therapy.
text.Response B: We recommend avoiding tight shoes, and regularly stretching your feet.
